Pragian public transport (MHD) will introduce the chip into their ticket system on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Prague Transportation Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will climb in the metro, trams and buses, which instead of having a paper ticket will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, it is accessible for about a hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a coupon for 30 days or 90 days (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and both register it on their chip card at the information points and offices of Dopravní podnik (the Transport Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nádra. Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letany, Kobylisy, Rajská Zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy coupons via the Internet on the website of Dopravní podnik: www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred people benefited from the service during the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can definitively forget the gateways in the metro stations, where they had to pedestrian in long queues so far to obtain paper tickets.
In fact, they will buy their coupon via the Internet and they will record it on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"On these points of contact, there is a access point with trained staff available to passengers, which will help interested parties purchase online and, moreover, will record the coupon they bought on their map," said the spokesperson of the Martin Opatrný project.
In addition to libraries, electronic coupons can also be recorded on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, reminding the machines to composter tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florence and Vltavská Metro Stations.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year there should be eighty," Opatrný added.
An automate will control the coupon instead of the driver
Machines that will operate from tomorrow are easy to use.
Just insert the Opencard chip card and the previously purchased coupon will register on the card itself.
Electronic coupons are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital, but also in the vicinity of the city.
In the periurban trains and bus lines 300 to 499, the inhabitants of the central Bohemian municipalities mainly use to access the capital.
"In the integrated trains in Pražská integrovaná doprava (integrated transport from Prague), the controllers are equipped with card readers, using which they establish the temporary and zonal validity of the coupons;" explained the control of the Filip Drápal tickets of the Ropid organization, which designs the timetables for public transport in Prague.
