The British newspaper Telegraph published an article that researchers at the University of Oxford have achieved an interesting experience analysing at what level belief in God could influence tolerance to human pain.
As part of this experience for the least strange, 12 Catholic believers and so many athletes were subjected to electrochocks, while each of them observed a painting representing the Virgin Mary.
