"The Committee is absolutely independent; all political, social and cultural ideas are represented in it - it would like to emphasise Alemanno - it would have to propose ideas for the development of Rome which could be used by the political decision-makers, which remain the Committee and the Municipal Council.
No superposition of roles, but only the desire to have a corner where to develop a great project for Rome.
In March, it will finish its tasks and then disappear, as this experience must have a specific time-limit.
In June-announces the Mayor- we will present the strategic plan resulting from the work carried out by the Commission for the future of Rome Capitale."
