The possibility of obtaining energy from sea movements has been studied for hundreds of years, and in the 1970s, in conjunction with the first oil crisis, research has intensified.
When the oil price declined around 1980, the idea of using marine energy was put off, but now the environmental authorities and the new increase in oil are making a major increase in the sector.
The London World Energy Council (WEC) estimated in 2007 that 15% of the global electricity demand could be covered by marine hop operating systems.
